field.name: SPI_MEM_SPI1_MST_ST
field.description: The current status of SPI1 master FSM.

field.name: SPI_MEM_MSPI_ST
field.description: The current status of SPI1 slave FSM: mspi_st. 0: idle state, 1: preparation state, 2: send command state, 3: send address state, 4: wait state, 5: read data state, 6:write data state, 7: done state, 8: read data end state.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PE
field.description: In user mode, it is set to indicate that program/erase operation will be triggered. The bit is combined with spi_mem_usr bit. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR
field.description: User define command enable. An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_HPM
field.description: Drive Flash into high performance mode. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RES
field.description: This bit combined with reg_resandres bit releases Flash from the power-down state or high performance mode and obtains the devices ID. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_DP
field.description: Drive Flash into power down. An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_CE
field.description: Chip erase enable. Chip erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_BE
field.description: Block erase enable(32KB) . Block erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_SE
field.description: Sector erase enable(4KB). Sector erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PP
field.description: Page program enable(1 byte ~256 bytes data to be programmed). Page program operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done .1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_WRSR
field.description: Write status register enable. Write status operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RDSR
field.description: Read status register-1. Read status operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RDID
field.description: Read JEDEC ID . Read ID command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_WRDI
field.description: Write flash disable. Write disable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_WREN
field.description: Write flash enable. Write enable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_READ
field.description: Read flash enable. Read flash operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_VALUE
field.description: In user mode, it is the memory address. other then the bit0-bit23 is the memory address, the bit24-bit31 are the byte length of a transfer.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CK_OUT_EDGE
field.description: the bit combined with spi_mem_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_DUAL
field.description: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals

field.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_QUAD
field.description: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals

field.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_DIO
field.description: In the write operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_QIO
field.description: In the write operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MISO_HIGHPART
field.description: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_mem_w8~spi_mem_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
field.description: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_mem_w8~spi_mem_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
field.description: SPI clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MOSI
field.description: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MISO
field.description: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY
field.description: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR
field.description: This bit enable the address phase of an operation.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND
field.description: This bit enable the command phase of an operation.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
field.description: The length in spi_mem_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
field.description: The value of command.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_OUT
field.description: In the dummy phase the signal level of spi is output by the spi controller.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_DUAL
field.description: Apply 2 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

field.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_QUAD
field.description: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

field.name: SPI_MEM_FCS_CRC_EN
field.description: For SPI1, initialize crc32 module before writing encrypted data to flash. Active low.

field.name: SPI_MEM_TX_CRC_EN
field.description: For SPI1, enable crc32 when writing encrypted data to flash. 1: enable 0:disable

field.name: SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE
field.description: This bit enable the bits: spi_mem_fread_qio, spi_mem_fread_dio, spi_mem_fread_qout and spi_mem_fread_dout. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL
field.description: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_RESANDRES
field.description: The Device ID is read out to SPI_MEM_RD_STATUS register, this bit combine with spi_mem_flash_res bit. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_Q_POL
field.description: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

field.name: SPI_MEM_D_POL
field.description: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD
field.description: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WP_REG
field.description: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WRSR_2B
field.description: two bytes data will be written to status register when it is set. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO
field.description: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO
field.description: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_MODE
field.description: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DLY_RES
field.description: After RES/DP/HPM command is sent, SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 512) SPI_CLK cycles.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SYNC_RESET
field.description: The FSM will be reset.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_L
field.description: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_H
field.description: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N
field.description: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
field.description: reserved

register.name: SPI_MEM_MOSI_DLEN_REG
register.description: SPI1 send data bit length control register.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MOSI_DBITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of write-data. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

register.name: SPI_MEM_MISO_DLEN_REG
register.description: SPI1 receive data bit length control register.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MISO_DBITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of read-data. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_STATUS
field.description: The value is stored when set spi_mem_flash_rdsr bit and spi_mem_flash_res bit.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WB_MODE
field.description: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS0_DIS
field.description: SPI_CS0 pin enable, 1: disable SPI_CS0, 0: SPI_CS0 pin is active to select SPI device, such as flash, external RAM and so on.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS1_DIS
field.description: SPI_CS1 pin enable, 1: disable SPI_CS1, 0: SPI_CS1 pin is active to select SPI device, such as flash, external RAM and so on.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE
field.description: 1: spi clk line is high when idle 0: spi clk line is low when idle

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
field.description: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_ADDR_4BYTE
field.description: For SPI1, cache read flash with 4 bytes address, 1: enable, 0:disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_DUAL
field.description: For SPI1, din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_DUAL
field.description: For SPI1, dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_DUAL
field.description: For SPI1, address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_QUAD
field.description: For SPI1, din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_QUAD
field.description: For SPI1, dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_QUAD
field.description: For SPI1, address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_DUMMY
field.description: The dummy phase enable when wait flash idle (RDSR)

field.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_CMD
field.description: The command to wait flash idle(RDSR).

field.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
field.description: The dummy cycle length when wait flash idle(RDSR).

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER
field.description: program erase resume bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES
field.description: program erase suspend bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN
field.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase resume command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase resume command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN
field.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase suspend command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase suspend command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PES_PER_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable PES end triggers PER transfer option. If this bit is 0, application should send PER after PES is done.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable Auto-suspending function.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PESR_END_MSK
field.description: The mask value when check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. If the read status value is status_in[15:0](only status_in[7:0] is valid when only one byte of data is read out, status_in[15:0] is valid when two bytes of data are read out), SUS/SUS1/SUS2 = status_in[15:0]^ SPI_MEM_PESR_END_MSK[15:0].

field.name: SPI_FMEM_RD_SUS_2B
field.description: 1: Read two bytes when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. 0: Read one byte when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit

field.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_EN
field.description: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the resume status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_EN
field.description: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the suspend status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT
field.description: When SPI1 checks SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits fail for SPI_MEM_SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT[6:0] times, it will be treated as check pass.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_COMMAND
field.description: Program/Erase resume command.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_COMMAND
field.description: Program/Erase suspend command.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND
field.description: Flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit read command. The command should be sent when SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit should be checked to insure the suspend or resume status of flash.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_SUS
field.description: The status of flash suspend, only used in SPI1.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_CMD_2B
field.description: 1: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[15:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit. 0: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[7:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_HPM_DLY_128
field.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RES_DLY_128
field.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_DP_DLY_128
field.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_DLY_128
field.description: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_DLY_128
field.description: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SPI0_LOCK_EN
field.description: 1: Enable SPI0 lock SPI0/1 arbiter option. 0: Disable it.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EN
field.description: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_TX_CRC_DATA
field.description: For SPI1, the value of crc32.

field.description: data buffer

field.description: data buffer

field.description: data buffer

field.description: data buffer

field.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI
field.description: The bit is used to enable timing auto-calibration for all reading operations.

field.name: SPI_MEM_EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
field.description: add extra dummy spi clock cycle length for spi clock calibration.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_CLR
field.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_CLR
field.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_CLR
field.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_CLR
field.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_CLR
field.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when Auto Resume command (0x7A) is sent and flash is resumed. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.1: Triggered when Auto Suspend command (0x75) is sent and flash is suspended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is sent and flash is already idle. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi1_slv_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. It means that SPI_CS raises high. 0: Others

field.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi1_mst_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_ST
field.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_ST
field.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_ST
field.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_ST
field.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_ST
field.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_MEM_DATE
field.description: Version control register

field.name: DMA_IN_DONE_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_IN_SUC_EOF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0. For UHCI0, the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_IN_ERR_EOF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 0. For other peripherals, this raw interrupt is reserved.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DONE_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been transmitted to peripherals for Tx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_OUT_EOF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been read from memory for Tx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_IN_DSCR_ERR_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting outlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of outlink descriptor for Tx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Rx buffer pointed by inlink is full and receiving data is not completed, but there is no more inlink for Rx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data corresponding a outlink (includes one link descriptor or few link descriptors) is transmitted out for Tx channel 0.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_OVF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_UDF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_OVF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Tx channel 0 is overflow.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_UDF_CH0_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Tx channel 0 is underflow.

field.name: DMA_IN_DONE_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the IN_DONE_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_IN_SUC_EOF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the IN_SUC_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_IN_ERR_EOF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the IN_ERR_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DONE_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_DONE_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_OUT_EOF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_IN_DSCR_ERR_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the IN_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_OVF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the INFIFO_OVF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_UDF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the INFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_OVF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUTFIFO_OVF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_UDF_CH0_INT_ST
field.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUTFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

field.name: DMA_IN_DONE_CH0_INT_ENA

field.name: DMA_IN_DONE_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_IN_SUC_EOF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 1. For UHCI0, the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_IN_ERR_EOF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 1. For other peripherals, this raw interrupt is reserved.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DONE_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been transmitted to peripherals for Tx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_OUT_EOF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been read from memory for Tx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_IN_DSCR_ERR_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting outlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of outlink descriptor for Tx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Rx buffer pointed by inlink is full and receiving data is not completed, but there is no more inlink for Rx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data corresponding a outlink (includes one link descriptor or few link descriptors) is transmitted out for Tx channel 1.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_OVF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 1 is overflow.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_UDF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 1 is underflow.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_OVF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Tx channel 1 is overflow.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_UDF_CH1_INT_RAW
field.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Tx channel 1 is underflow.

field.name: DMA_IN_RST_CH0
field.description: This bit is used to reset DMA channel 0 Rx FSM and Rx FIFO pointer.

field.name: DMA_IN_LOOP_TEST_CH0
field.description: reserved

field.name: DMA_INDSCR_BURST_EN_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

field.name: DMA_IN_DATA_BURST_EN_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 receiving data when accessing internal SRAM.

field.name: DMA_MEM_TRANS_EN_CH0
field.description: Set this bit 1 to enable automatic transmitting data from memory to memory via DMA.

field.name: DMA_IN_CHECK_OWNER_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_RDATA_CH0
field.description: This register stores the data popping from DMA FIFO.

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_POP_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to pop data from DMA FIFO.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_ADDR_CH0
field.description: This register stores the 20 least significant bits of the first inlink descriptor's address.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_AUTO_RET_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to return to current inlink descriptor's address, when there are some errors in current receiving data.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_STOP_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the inlink descriptors.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_START_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the inlink descriptors.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_RESTART_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to mount a new inlink descriptor.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_PARK_CH0
field.description: 1: the inlink descriptor's FSM is in idle state. 0: the inlink descriptor's FSM is working.

field.name: DMA_OUT_RST_CH0
field.description: This bit is used to reset DMA channel 0 Tx FSM and Tx FIFO pointer.

field.name: DMA_OUT_LOOP_TEST_CH0
field.description: reserved

field.name: DMA_OUT_AUTO_WRBACK_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to enable automatic outlink-writeback when all the data in tx buffer has been transmitted.

field.name: DMA_OUT_EOF_MODE_CH0
field.description: EOF flag generation mode when transmitting data. 1: EOF flag for Tx channel 0 is generated when data need to transmit has been popped from FIFO in DMA

field.name: DMA_OUTDSCR_BURST_EN_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

field.name: DMA_OUT_DATA_BURST_EN_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 0 transmitting data when accessing internal SRAM.

field.name: DMA_OUT_CHECK_OWNER_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_WDATA_CH0
field.description: This register stores the data that need to be pushed into DMA FIFO.

field.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_PUSH_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to push data into DMA FIFO.

field.name: DMA_OUTLINK_ADDR_CH0
field.description: This register stores the 20 least significant bits of the first outlink descriptor's address.

field.name: DMA_OUTLINK_STOP_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the outlink descriptors.

field.name: DMA_OUTLINK_START_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the outlink descriptors.

field.name: DMA_OUTLINK_RESTART_CH0
field.description: Set this bit to restart a new outlink from the last address.

field.name: DMA_OUTLINK_PARK_CH0
field.description: 1: the outlink descriptor's FSM is in idle state. 0: the outlink descriptor's FSM is working.

field.name: DMA_IN_RST_CH1
field.description: This bit is used to reset DMA channel 1 Rx FSM and Rx FIFO pointer.

field.name: DMA_IN_LOOP_TEST_CH1
field.description: reserved

field.name: DMA_INDSCR_BURST_EN_CH1

field.name: DMA_IN_DATA_BURST_EN_CH1
field.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 1 receiving data when accessing internal SRAM.

field.name: DMA_MEM_TRANS_EN_CH1

field.name: DMA_INFIFO_POP_CH1

field.name: DMA_INLINK_ADDR_CH1

field.name: DMA_INLINK_AUTO_RET_CH1
field.description: Set this bit to return to current inlink descriptor's address, when there are some errors in current receiving data.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_STOP_CH1
field.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the inlink descriptors.

field.name: DMA_INLINK_START_CH1

field.name: DMA_OUT_AUTO_WRBACK_CH1

field.name: IO_MUX_CLK_OUT1
field.description: If you want to output clock for I2S to CLK_OUT_out1, set this register to 0x0. CLK_OUT_out1 can be found in peripheral output signals.

field.name: IO_MUX_CLK_OUT2
field.description: If you want to output clock for I2S to CLK_OUT_out2, set this register to 0x0. CLK_OUT_out2 can be found in peripheral output signals.

field.name: IO_MUX_CLK_OUT3
field.description: If you want to output clock for I2S to CLK_OUT_out3, set this register to 0x0. CLK_OUT_out3 can be found in peripheral output signals.

register.name: IO_MUX_GPIO%s_REG
register.description: IO MUX Configure Register for pad XTAL_32K_P

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_MCU_OE
field.description: Output enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: output enabled; 0: output disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_SLP_SEL
field.description: Sleep mode selection of this pad. Set to 1 to put the pad in pad mode.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_MCU_WPD
field.description: Pull-down enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: internal pull-down enabled; 0: internal pull-down disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_MCU_WPU
field.description: Pull-up enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: internal pull-up enabled; 0: internal pull-up disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_MCU_IE
field.description: Input enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: input enabled; 0: input disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_FUN_WPD
field.description: Pull-down enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-down enabled; 0: internal pull-down disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_FUN_WPU
field.description: Pull-up enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-up enabled; 0: internal pull-up disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_FUN_IE
field.description: Input enable of the pad. 1: input enabled; 0: input disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_FUN_DRV
field.description: Select the drive strength of the pad. 0: ~5 mA; 1: ~10mA; 2: ~20mA; 3: ~40mA.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_MCU_SEL
field.description: Select IO MUX function for this signal. 0: Select Function 1; 1: Select Function 2; etc.

field.name: IO_MUX_GPIO$n_FILTER_EN
field.description: Enable filter for pin input signals. 1: Filter enabled; 2: Filter disabled.

field.name: IO_MUX_REG_DATE
field.description: Version control register

field.name: DS_SET_START
field.description: set this bit to start DS operation.

field.name: DS_SET_CONTINUE
field.description: set this bit to continue DS operation.

field.name: DS_SET_FINISH
field.description: Set this bit to finish DS process.

field.name: DS_QUERY_BUSY
field.description: digital signature state. 1'b0: idle, 1'b1: busy

field.name: DS_QUERY_KEY_WRONG
field.description: digital signature key wrong counter

field.name: DS_MD_ERROR
field.description: MD checkout result. 1'b0: MD check pass, 1'b1: MD check fail

field.name: DS_PADDING_BAD
field.description: padding checkout result. 1'b0: a good padding, 1'b1: a bad padding

field.name: DS_DATE
field.description: ds version information

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_START_FORCE
field.description: select software enable saradc sample

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_START
field.description: software enable saradc sample

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_SAR_CLK_GATED
field.description: SAR clock gated

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_SAR_CLK_DIV
field.description: SAR clock divider

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_SAR_PATT_LEN
field.description: 0 ~ 15 means length 1 ~ 16

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_SAR_PATT_P_CLEAR
field.description: clear the pointer of pattern table for DIG ADC1 CTRL

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_XPD_SAR_FORCE
field.description: force option to xpd sar blocks

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_WAIT_ARB_CYCLE
field.description: wait arbit signal stable after sar_done

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_MEAS_NUM_LIMIT
field.description: enable max meas num

field.name: APB_SARADC_SARADC_MAX_MEAS_NUM
field.description: max conversion number

field.name: UHCI_TX_RST
field.description: Write 1, then write 0 to this bit to reset decode state machine.

field.name: UHCI_RX_RST
field.description: Write 1, then write 0 to this bit to reset encode state machine.

field.name: UHCI_UART0_CE
field.description: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART0.

field.name: UHCI_UART1_CE
field.description: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART1.

field.name: UHCI_SEPER_EN
field.description: Set this bit to separate the data frame using a special char.

field.name: UHCI_HEAD_EN
field.description: Set this bit to encode the data packet with a formatting header.

field.name: UHCI_CRC_REC_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable UHCI to receive the 16 bit CRC.

field.name: UHCI_UART_IDLE_EOF_EN
field.description: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI will end the payload receiving process when UART has been in idle state.

field.name: UHCI_LEN_EOF_EN
field.description: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI decoder receiving payload data is end when the receiving byte count has reached the specified value. The value is payload length indicated by UHCI packet header when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 1 or the value is configuration value when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 0. If this bit is set to 0, UHCI decoder receiving payload data is end when 0xc0 is received.

field.name: UHCI_ENCODE_CRC_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable data integrity checking by appending a 16 bit CCITT-CRC to end of the payload.

field.name: UHCI_CLK_EN
field.description: 1'b1: Force clock on for register. 1'b0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

field.name: UHCI_UART_RX_BRK_EOF_EN
field.description: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI will end payload receive process when NULL frame is received by UART.

field.name: AES_MODE
field.description: This bits decides which one operation mode will be used. 3'd0: AES-EN-128, 3'd1: AES-EN-192, 3'd2: AES-EN-256, 3'd4: AES-DE-128, 3'd5: AES-DE-192, 3'd6: AES-DE-256.

field.name: AES_ENDIAN
field.description: endian. [1:0] key endian, [3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian, [5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian

field.name: AES_BLOCK_MODE
field.description: Those bits decides which block mode will be used. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: GCM, 0x7: reserved.

field.name: AES_BLOCK_NUM
field.description: Those bits stores the number of Plaintext/ciphertext block.

field.name: AES_INC_SEL
field.description: This bit decides the standard incrementing function. 0: INC32. 1: INC128.

register.name: AES_AAD_BLOCK_NUM_REG
register.description: Additional Authential Data block number register

field.name: AES_AAD_BLOCK_NUM
field.description: Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

field.name: AES_REMAINDER_BIT_NUM
field.description: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

field.name: AES_TRIGGER
field.description: Set this bit to start AES calculation.

field.name: AES_STATE
field.description: Those bits shows AES status. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

field.name: AES_DMA_ENABLE
field.description: 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

field.name: AES_CONTINUE
field.description: Set this bit to continue GCM operation.

field.name: AES_DMA_EXIT
field.description: Set this register to leave calculation done stage. Recommend to use it after software finishes reading DMA's output buffer.

register.name: AES_IV_MEM
register.description: The memory that stores initialization vector

register.name: AES_H_MEM
register.description: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

field.description: Set this bit to clear the AES interrupt.

field.description: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when DMA-AES calculation is done.

field.name: AES_DATE
field.description: This bits stores the version information of AES.

field.name: RSA_SEARCH_ENABLE
field.description: Configure this bit to 1 for acceleration. 1: with acceleration, 0: without acceleration(default). This option should be used together with RSA_SEARCH_POS.

field.name: RSA_SEARCH_POS
field.description: Configure this field to set search position. This field should be used together with RSA_SEARCH_ENABLE. The field is only meaningful when RSA_SEARCH_ENABLE is high.

field.description: query rsa idle. 1'b0: busy, 1'b1: idle

field.description: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when rsa calculation is done. 1'b0: disable, 1'b1: enable(default).

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_RD_BYTE
field.description: UART $n accesses FIFO via this register.

field.name: UART_RX_SIZE
field.description: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for receive-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

field.name: UART_TX_SIZE
field.description: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for transmit-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

field.name: UART_RX_FLOW_THRHD
field.description: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received when hardware flow control works.

field.name: UART_RX_TOUT_THRHD
field.description: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

field.name: UART_MEM_FORCE_PD
field.description: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

field.name: UART_MEM_FORCE_PU
field.description: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than what rxfifo_full_thrhd specifies.

field.name: UART_TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in Tx-FIFO is less than what txfifo_empty_thrhd specifies .

field.name: UART_PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error in the data.

field.name: UART_FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error .

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the FIFO can store.

field.name: UART_DSR_CHG_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

field.name: UART_CTS_CHG_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of CTSn signal.

field.name: UART_BRK_DET_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

field.name: UART_SW_XON_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver recevies Xon char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

field.name: UART_SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives Xoff char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

field.name: UART_GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

field.name: UART_TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes sending NULL characters, after all data in Tx-FIFO are sent.

field.name: UART_TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the last data.

field.name: UART_TX_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send out all data in FIFO.

field.name: UART_RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error from the echo of transmitter in rs485 mode.

field.name: UART_RS485_FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error from the echo of transmitter in rs485 mode.

field.name: UART_RS485_CLASH_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when detects a clash between transmitter and receiver in rs485 mode.

field.name: UART_AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the configured at_cmd char.

field.name: UART_WAKEUP_INT_RAW
field.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when input rxd edge changes more times than what reg_active_threshold specifies in light sleeping mode.

field.name: UART_WAKEUP_INT_CLR
field.description: Set this bit to clear the uart_wakeup_int_raw interrupt.

field.name: UART_CLKDIV
field.description: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

field.name: UART_CLKDIV_FRAG
field.description: The decimal part of the frequency divider factor.

field.name: UART_GLITCH_FILT
field.description: when input pulse width is lower than this value, the pulse is ignored.

field.name: UART_GLITCH_FILT_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable Rx signal filter.

field.name: UART_PARITY
field.description: This register is used to configure the parity check mode.

field.name: UART_PARITY_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable uart parity check.

field.name: UART_BIT_NUM
field.description: This register is used to set the length of data.

field.name: UART_STOP_BIT_NUM
field.description: This register is used to set the length of stop bit.

field.name: UART_SW_RTS
field.description: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

field.name: UART_SW_DTR
field.description: This register is used to configure the software dtr signal which is used in software flow control.

field.name: UART_TXD_BRK
field.description: Set this bit to enbale transmitter to send NULL when the process of sending data is done.

field.name: UART_IRDA_DPLX
field.description: Set this bit to enable IrDA loopback mode.

field.name: UART_IRDA_TX_EN
field.description: This is the start enable bit for IrDA transmitter.

field.name: UART_IRDA_WCTL
field.description: 1'h1: The IrDA transmitter's 11th bit is the same as 10th bit. 1'h0: Set IrDA transmitter's 11th bit to 0.

field.name: UART_IRDA_TX_INV
field.description: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA transmitter.

field.name: UART_IRDA_RX_INV
field.description: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA receiver.

field.name: UART_LOOPBACK
field.description: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

field.name: UART_TX_FLOW_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable flow control function for transmitter.

field.name: UART_IRDA_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable IrDA protocol.

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_RST
field.description: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

field.name: UART_TXFIFO_RST
field.description: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

field.name: UART_RXD_INV
field.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

field.name: UART_CTS_INV
field.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

field.name: UART_DSR_INV
field.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

field.name: UART_TXD_INV
field.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

field.name: UART_RTS_INV
field.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

field.name: UART_DTR_INV
field.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

field.name: UART_CLK_EN
field.description: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

field.name: UART_ERR_WR_MASK
field.description: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the received data is wrong.

field.name: UART_AUTOBAUD_EN
field.description: This is the enable bit for detecting baudrate.

field.name: UART_MEM_CLK_EN
field.description: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
field.description: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

field.name: UART_TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
field.description: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

field.name: UART_DIS_RX_DAT_OVF
field.description: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

field.name: UART_RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
field.description: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

field.name: UART_RX_FLOW_EN
field.description: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

field.name: UART_RX_TOUT_EN
field.description: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

field.name: UART_SW_FLOW_CON_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

field.name: UART_XONOFF_DEL
field.description: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

field.name: UART_FORCE_XON
field.description: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

field.name: UART_FORCE_XOFF
field.description: Set this bit to stop the transmitter from sending data.

field.name: UART_SEND_XON
field.description: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

field.name: UART_SEND_XOFF
field.description: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

field.name: UART_ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
field.description: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

field.name: UART_XOFF_THRESHOLD
field.description: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xoff char.

field.name: UART_XOFF_CHAR
field.description: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

field.name: UART_XON_THRESHOLD
field.description: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xon char.

field.name: UART_XON_CHAR
field.description: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

field.name: UART_TX_BRK_NUM
field.description: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

field.name: UART_RX_IDLE_THRHD
field.description: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

field.name: UART_TX_IDLE_NUM
field.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

field.name: UART_RS485_EN
field.description: Set this bit to choose the rs485 mode.

field.name: UART_DL0_EN
field.description: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

field.name: UART_DL1_EN
field.description: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

field.name: UART_RS485TX_RX_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable receiver could receive data when the transmitter is transmitting data in rs485 mode.

field.name: UART_RS485RXBY_TX_EN
field.description: 1'h1: enable rs485 transmitter to send data when rs485 receiver line is busy.

field.name: UART_RS485_RX_DLY_NUM
field.description: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

field.name: UART_RS485_TX_DLY_NUM
field.description: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

field.name: UART_SCLK_DIV_B
field.description: The denominator of the frequency divider factor.

field.name: UART_SCLK_DIV_A
field.description: The numerator of the frequency divider factor.

field.name: UART_SCLK_DIV_NUM
field.description: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

field.name: UART_SCLK_SEL
field.description: UART clock source select. 1: 80Mhz, 2: 8Mhz, 3: XTAL.

field.name: UART_SCLK_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable UART Tx/Rx clock.

field.name: UART_RST_CORE
field.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx/Rx.

field.name: UART_TX_SCLK_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

field.name: UART_RX_SCLK_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

field.name: UART_TX_RST_CORE
field.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx.

field.name: UART_RX_RST_CORE
field.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Rx.

field.name: UART_RXFIFO_CNT
field.description: Stores the byte number of valid data in Rx-FIFO.

field.name: UART_DSRN
field.description: The register represent the level value of the internal uart dsr signal.

field.name: UART_CTSN
field.description: This register represent the level value of the internal uart cts signal.

field.name: UART_RXD
field.description: This register represent the level value of the internal uart rxd signal.

field.name: UART_TXFIFO_CNT
field.description: Stores the byte number of data in Tx-FIFO.

field.name: UART_DTRN
field.description: This bit represents the level of the internal uart dtr signal.

field.name: UART_RTSN
field.description: This bit represents the level of the internal uart rts signal.

field.name: UART_TXD
field.description: This bit represents the level of the internal uart txd signal.

register.name: UART_MEM_TX_STATUS_REG
register.description: Tx-FIFO write and read offset address.

field.name: UART_APB_TX_WADDR
field.description: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when software writes Tx-FIFO via APB.

field.name: UART_TX_RADDR
field.description: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when Tx-FSM reads data via Tx-FIFO_Ctrl.

register.name: UART_MEM_RX_STATUS_REG
register.description: Rx-FIFO write and read offset address.

field.name: UART_APB_RX_RADDR
field.description: This register stores the offset address in RX-FIFO when software reads data from Rx-FIFO via APB. UART0 is 10'h100. UART1 is 10'h180.

field.name: UART_RX_WADDR
field.description: This register stores the offset address in Rx-FIFO when Rx-FIFO_Ctrl writes Rx-FIFO. UART0 is 10'h100. UART1 is 10'h180.

field.name: UART_ST_URX_OUT
field.description: This is the status register of receiver.

field.name: UART_ST_UTX_OUT
field.description: This is the status register of transmitter.

register.name: UART_LOWPULSE_REG
register.description: Autobaud minimum low pulse duration register

field.name: UART_LOWPULSE_MIN_CNT
field.description: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time of the low level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

register.name: UART_HIGHPULSE_REG
register.description: Autobaud minimum high pulse duration register

field.name: UART_HIGHPULSE_MIN_CNT
field.description: This register stores the value of the maxinum duration time for the high level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

field.name: UART_RXD_EDGE_CNT
field.description: This register stores the count of rxd edge change. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

field.name: UART_POSEDGE_MIN_CNT
field.description: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two positive edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

field.name: UART_NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT
field.description: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two negative edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

field.name: UART_PRE_IDLE_NUM
field.description: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

field.name: UART_POST_IDLE_NUM
field.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

field.name: UART_RX_GAP_TOUT
field.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

field.name: UART_AT_CMD_CHAR
field.description: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

field.name: UART_CHAR_NUM
field.description: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

field.name: UART_DATE
field.description: This is the version register.

field.name: UART_ID
field.description: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

field.name: UART_HIGH_SPEED
field.description: This bit used to select synchronize mode. 1: Registers are auto synchronized into UART Core clock and UART core should be keep the same with APB clock. 0: After configure registers, software needs to write 1 to UART_REG_UPDATE to synchronize registers.

field.name: UART_REG_UPDATE
field.description: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

field.name: XTS_AES_LINESIZE
field.description: This bit stores the line size parameter. 0: 16Byte, 1: 32Byte.

field.name: XTS_AES_DESTINATION
field.description: This bit stores the destination. 0: flash(default). 1: reserved.

field.name: XTS_AES_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS
field.description: Those bits stores the physical address. If linesize is 16-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 16 bytes. If linesize is 32-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 32 bytes.

field.name: XTS_AES_TRIGGER
field.description: Set this bit to start manual encryption calculation

field.name: XTS_AES_RELEASE
field.description: Set this bit to release the manual encrypted result, after that the result will be visible to spi

field.name: XTS_AES_DESTROY
field.description: Set this bit to destroy XTS-AES result.

field.name: XTS_AES_STATE
field.description: Those bits shows XTS-AES status. 0=IDLE, 1=WORK, 2=RELEASE, 3=USE. IDLE means that XTS-AES is idle. WORK means that XTS-AES is busy with calculation. RELEASE means the encrypted result is generated but not visible to mspi. USE means that the encrypted result is visible to mspi.

field.name: XTS_AES_DATE
field.description: Those bits stores the version information of XTS-AES.

field.name: SPI_CONF_BITLEN
field.description: Define the APB cycles of SPI_CONF state. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_UPDATE
field.description: Set this bit to synchronize SPI registers from APB clock domain into SPI module clock domain, which is only used in SPI master mode.

field.name: SPI_USR
field.description: User define command enable. An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable. Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

field.name: SPI_USR_ADDR_VALUE
field.description: Address to slave. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DOUTDIN
field.description: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_QPI_MODE
field.description: Both for master mode and slave mode. 1: spi controller is in QPI mode. 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_TSCK_I_EDGE
field.description: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of tsck. 0: tsck = spi_ck_i. 1:tsck = !spi_ck_i.

field.name: SPI_CS_HOLD
field.description: spi cs keep low when spi is in done phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS_SETUP
field.description: spi cs is enable when spi is in prepare phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_RSCK_I_EDGE
field.description: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of rsck. 0: rsck = !spi_ck_i. 1:rsck = spi_ck_i.

field.name: SPI_CK_OUT_EDGE
field.description: the bit combined with spi_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FWRITE_DUAL
field.description: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FWRITE_QUAD
field.description: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_CONF_NXT
field.description: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of next seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will continue. 0: The seg-trans will end after the current SPI seg-trans or this is not seg-trans mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_SIO
field.description: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_MISO_HIGHPART
field.description: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
field.description: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
field.description: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_MOSI
field.description: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_MISO
field.description: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_DUMMY
field.description: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_ADDR
field.description: This bit enable the address phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_COMMAND
field.description: This bit enable the command phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
field.description: The length in spi_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_MST_WFULL_ERR_END_EN
field.description: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

field.name: SPI_CS_SETUP_TIME
field.description: (cycles+1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_setup bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS_HOLD_TIME
field.description: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_hold bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
field.description: The value of command. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_MST_REMPTY_ERR_END_EN
field.description: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

field.name: SPI_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DUMMY_OUT
field.description: In the dummy phase the signal level of spi is output by the spi controller. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FADDR_DUAL
field.description: Apply 2 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FADDR_QUAD
field.description: Apply 4 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FCMD_DUAL
field.description: Apply 2 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FCMD_QUAD
field.description: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FREAD_DUAL
field.description: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_FREAD_QUAD
field.description: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_Q_POL
field.description: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_D_POL
field.description: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_HOLD_POL
field.description: SPI_HOLD output value when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_WP_POL
field.description: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_RD_BIT_ORDER
field.description: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_WR_BIT_ORDER
field.description: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

register.name: SPI_MS_DLEN_REG
register.description: SPI data bit length control register

field.name: SPI_MS_DATA_BITLEN
field.description: The value of these bits is the configured SPI transmission data bit length in master mode DMA controlled transfer or CPU controlled transfer. The value is also the configured bit length in slave mode DMA RX controlled transfer. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS0_DIS
field.description: SPI CS$n pin enable, 1: disable CS$n, 0: spi_cs$n signal is from/to CS$n pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS1_DIS
field.description: SPI CS$n pin enable, 1: disable CS$n, 0: spi_cs$n signal is from/to CS$n pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS2_DIS
field.description: SPI CS$n pin enable, 1: disable CS$n, 0: spi_cs$n signal is from/to CS$n pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS3_DIS
field.description: SPI CS$n pin enable, 1: disable CS$n, 0: spi_cs$n signal is from/to CS$n pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS4_DIS
field.description: SPI CS$n pin enable, 1: disable CS$n, 0: spi_cs$n signal is from/to CS$n pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS5_DIS
field.description: SPI CS$n pin enable, 1: disable CS$n, 0: spi_cs$n signal is from/to CS$n pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CK_DIS
field.description: 1: spi clk out disable, 0: spi clk out enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_MASTER_CS_POL
field.description: In the master mode the bits are the polarity of spi cs line, the value is equivalent to spi_cs ^ spi_master_cs_pol. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_SLAVE_CS_POL
field.description: spi slave input cs polarity select. 1: inv 0: not change. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CK_IDLE_EDGE
field.description: 1: spi clk line is high when idle 0: spi clk line is low when idle. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
field.description: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_QUAD_DIN_PIN_SWAP
field.description: 1: spi quad input swap enable 0: spi quad input swap disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DMA_SLV_SEG_TRANS_EN
field.description: Enable dma segment transfer in spi dma half slave mode. 1: enable. 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_SLV_RX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN
field.description: 1: spi_dma_infifo_full_vld is cleared by spi slave cmd 5. 0: spi_dma_infifo_full_vld is cleared by spi_trans_done.

field.name: SPI_SLV_TX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN
field.description: 1: spi_dma_outfifo_empty_vld is cleared by spi slave cmd 6. 0: spi_dma_outfifo_empty_vld is cleared by spi_trans_done.

field.name: SPI_RX_EOF_EN
field.description: 1: spi_dma_inlink_eof is set when the number of dma pushed data bytes is equal to the value of spi_slv/mst_dma_rd_bytelen[19:0] in spi dma transition. 0: spi_dma_inlink_eof is set by spi_trans_done in non-seg-trans or spi_dma_seg_trans_done in seg-trans.

field.name: SPI_DMA_RX_ENA
field.description: Set this bit to enable SPI DMA controlled receive data mode.

field.name: SPI_DMA_TX_ENA
field.description: Set this bit to enable SPI DMA controlled send data mode.

field.name: SPI_RX_AFIFO_RST
field.description: Set this bit to reset RX AFIFO, which is used to receive data in SPI master and slave mode transfer.

field.name: SPI_BUF_AFIFO_RST
field.description: Set this bit to reset BUF TX AFIFO, which is used send data out in SPI slave CPU controlled mode transfer and master mode transfer.

field.name: SPI_DMA_AFIFO_RST
field.description: Set this bit to reset DMA TX AFIFO, which is used to send data out in SPI slave DMA controlled mode transfer.

field.name: SPI_CLK_MODE
field.description: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CLK_MODE_13
field.description: {CPOL, CPHA},1: support spi clk mode 1 and 3, first edge output data B[0]/B[7]. 0: support spi clk mode 0 and 2, first edge output data B[1]/B[6].

field.name: SPI_RSCK_DATA_OUT
field.description: It saves half a cycle when tsck is the same as rsck. 1: output data at rsck posedge 0: output data at tsck posedge

field.name: SPI_SLV_RDDMA_BITLEN_EN
field.description: 1: SPI_SLV_DATA_BITLEN stores data bit length of master-read-slave data length in DMA controlled mode(Rd_DMA). 0: others

field.name: SPI_SLV_WRDMA_BITLEN_EN
field.description: 1: SPI_SLV_DATA_BITLEN stores data bit length of master-write-to-slave data length in DMA controlled mode(Wr_DMA). 0: others

field.name: SPI_SLV_RDBUF_BITLEN_EN
field.description: 1: SPI_SLV_DATA_BITLEN stores data bit length of master-read-slave data length in CPU controlled mode(Rd_BUF). 0: others

field.name: SPI_SLV_WRBUF_BITLEN_EN
field.description: 1: SPI_SLV_DATA_BITLEN stores data bit length of master-write-to-slave data length in CPU controlled mode(Wr_BUF). 0: others

field.name: SPI_DMA_SEG_MAGIC_VALUE
field.description: The magic value of BM table in master DMA seg-trans.

field.name: SPI_SLAVE_MODE
field.description: Set SPI work mode. 1: slave mode 0: master mode.

field.name: SPI_SOFT_RESET
field.description: Software reset enable, reset the spi clock line cs line and data lines. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_USR_CONF
field.description: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of current seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will start. 0: This is not seg-trans mode.

field.name: SPI_SLV_DATA_BITLEN
field.description: The transferred data bit length in SPI slave FD and HD mode.

field.name: SPI_SLV_LAST_COMMAND
field.description: In the slave mode it is the value of command.

field.name: SPI_SLV_LAST_ADDR
field.description: In the slave mode it is the value of address.

field.name: SPI_CLKCNT_L
field.description: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_clkcnt_N. In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CLKCNT_H
field.description: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CLKCNT_N
field.description: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(spi_clkdiv_pre+1)/(spi_clkcnt_N+1). Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CLKDIV_PRE
field.description: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
field.description: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock. Can be configured in CONF state.

register.name: SPI_CLK_GATE_REG
register.description: SPI module clock and register clock control

field.name: SPI_CLK_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable clk gate

field.name: SPI_MST_CLK_ACTIVE
field.description: Set this bit to power on the SPI module clock.

field.name: SPI_MST_CLK_SEL
field.description: This bit is used to select SPI module clock source in master mode. 1: PLL_CLK_80M. 0: XTAL CLK.

field.name: SPI_DIN0_MODE
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN1_MODE
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN2_MODE
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN3_MODE
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_TIMING_HCLK_ACTIVE
field.description: 1:enable hclk in SPI input timing module. 0: disable it. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN0_NUM
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,... Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN1_NUM
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,... Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN2_NUM
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,... Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DIN3_NUM
field.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,... Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DOUT0_MODE
field.description: The output signal $n is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DOUT1_MODE
field.description: The output signal $n is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DOUT2_MODE
field.description: The output signal $n is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DOUT3_MODE
field.description: The output signal $n is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

field.name: SPI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_ERR_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_ERR_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_DMA_OUTFIFO_EMPTY_ERR_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI_DMA_OUTFIFO_EMPTY_ERR_INT interrupt.

field.name: SPI_SLV_EX_QPI_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI slave Ex_QPI interrupt.

field.name: SPI_SLV_EN_QPI_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI slave En_QPI interrupt.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD7_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI slave CMD7 interrupt.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD8_INT_ENA
field.description: The enable bit for SPI slave CMD8 interrupt.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD9_INT_ENA

field.name: SPI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: 1: The current data rate of DMA Rx is smaller than that of SPI, which will lose the receive data. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_DMA_OUTFIFO_EMPTY_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: 1: The current data rate of DMA TX is smaller than that of SPI. SPI will stop in master mode and send out all 0 in slave mode. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_EX_QPI_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI slave Ex_QPI interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Ex_QPI transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_EN_QPI_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI slave En_QPI interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode En_QPI transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD7_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI slave CMD7 interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMD7 transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD8_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI slave CMD8 interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMD8 transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD9_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI slave CMD9 interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMD9 transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMDA_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI slave CMDA interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMDA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_RD_DMA_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_RD_DMA_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Rd_DMA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_WR_DMA_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_WR_DMA_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Wr_DMA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_RD_BUF_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_RD_BUF_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Rd_BUF transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_WR_BUF_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_WR_BUF_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Wr_BUF transmission is ended. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_TRANS_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_TRANS_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI master mode transmission is ended. 0: others.

field.name: SPI_DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: spi master DMA full-duplex/half-duplex seg-conf-trans ends or slave half-duplex seg-trans ends. And data has been pushed to corresponding memory. 0: seg-conf-trans or seg-trans is not ended or not occurred.

field.name: SPI_SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The magic value in CONF buffer is error in the DMA seg-conf-trans. 0: others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_BUF_ADDR_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_BUF_ADDR_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The accessing data address of the current SPI slave mode CPU controlled FD, Wr_BUF or Rd_BUF transmission is bigger than 63. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_SLV_CMD_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_CMD_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The slave command value in the current SPI slave HD mode transmission is not supported. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_MST_RX_AFIFO_WFULL_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MST_RX_AFIFO_WFULL_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: There is a RX AFIFO write-full error when SPI inputs data in master mode. 0: Others.

field.name: SPI_MST_TX_AFIFO_REMPTY_ERR_INT_RAW
field.description: The raw bit for SPI_MST_TX_AFIFO_REMPTY_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: There is a TX BUF AFIFO read-empty error when SPI outputs data in master mode. 0: Others.

field.description: The raw bit for SPI_APP1_INT interrupt. The value is only controlled by application.
