field.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_OUT
field.description: In the dummy phase the signal level of spi is output by the spi controller.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_DUAL
field.description: Apply 2 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

field.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_QUAD
field.description: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

field.name: SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE
field.description: This bit enable the bits: spi_mem_fread_qio, spi_mem_fread_dio, spi_mem_fread_qout and spi_mem_fread_dout. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL
field.description: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_Q_POL
field.description: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

field.name: SPI_MEM_D_POL
field.description: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD
field.description: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_WP_REG
field.description: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO
field.description: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO
field.description: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_MODE
field.description: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on.

field.name: SPI_MEM_RXFIFO_RST
field.description: SPI0 RX FIFO reset signal.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP_TIME
field.description: (cycles-1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_mem_cs_setup bit.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME
field.description: Spi cs signal is delayed to inactive by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_mem_cs_hold bit.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY
field.description: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to flash. tSHSL is (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SYNC_RESET
field.description: The FSM will be reset.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_L
field.description: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_H
field.description: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N
field.description: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
field.description: Set this bit in 1-division mode.

field.name: SPI_MEM_TRANS_END
field.description: The bit is used to indicate the spi0_mst_st controlled transmitting is done.

field.name: SPI_MEM_TRANS_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The bit is used to enable the interrupt of spi0_mst_st controlled transmitting is done.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CSPI_ST_TRANS_END
field.description: The bit is used to indicate the spi0_slv_st controlled transmitting is done.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CSPI_ST_TRANS_END_INT_ENA
field.description: The bit is used to enable the interrupt of spi0_slv_st controlled transmitting is done.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE
field.description: 1: spi clk line is high when idle 0: spi clk line is low when idle

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
field.description: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_REQ_EN
field.description: For SPI0, Cache access enable, 1: enable, 0:disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_ADDR_4BYTE
field.description: For SPI0, cache read flash with 4 bytes address, 1: enable, 0:disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_FLASH_USR_CMD
field.description: For SPI0, cache read flash for user define command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_DUAL
field.description: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_DUAL
field.description: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_DUAL
field.description: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_QUAD
field.description: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_QUAD
field.description: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_QUAD
field.description: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EN
field.description: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_SPI01_CLK_SEL
field.description: When the digital system clock selects PLL clock and the frequency of PLL clock is 480MHz, the value of reg_spi01_clk_sel: 0: SPI0/1 module clock (clk) is 80MHz. 1: SPI0/1 module clock (clk) is 120MHz. 2: SPI0/1 module clock (clk) 160MHz. 3: Not used. When the digital system clock selects PLL clock and the frequency of PLL clock is 320MHz, the value of reg_spi01_clk_sel: 0: SPI0/1 module clock (clk) is 80MHz. 1: SPI0/1 module clock (clk) is 80MHz. 2: SPI0/1 module clock (clk) 160MHz. 3: Not used.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD
field.description: spi cs keep low when spi is in done phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP
field.description: spi cs is enable when spi is in prepare phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CK_OUT_EDGE
field.description: the bit combined with spi_mem_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
field.description: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY
field.description: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
field.description: The length in spi_mem_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
field.description: The value of command.

field.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
field.description: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

field.name: SPI_MEM_WB_MODE
field.description: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CSPI_ST
field.description: The current status of SPI0 slave FSM: spi0_slv_st. 0: idle state, 1: preparation state, 2: send command state, 3: send address state, 4: wait state, 5: read data state, 6:write data state, 7: done state, 8: read data end state.

field.name: SPI_MEM_EM_ST
field.description: The current status of SPI0 master FSM: spi0_mst_st. 0: idle state, 1:EM_CACHE_GRANT , 2: program/erase suspend state, 3: SPI0 read data state, 4: wait cache/EDMA sent data is stored in SPI0 TX FIFO, 5: SPI0 write data state.

field.name: SPI_MEM_CSPI_LOCK_DELAY_TIME
field.description: The lock delay time of SPI0/1 arbiter by spi0_slv_st, after PER is sent by SPI1.

field.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CLK_ENA
field.description: The bit is used to enable timing adjust clock for all reading operations.

field.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI
field.description: The bit is used to enable timing auto-calibration for all reading operations.

field.name: SPI_MEM_EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
field.description: add extra dummy spi clock cycle length for spi clock calibration.

field.name: EFUSE_WR_DIS
field.description: Disable programming of individual eFuses.

field.name: EFUSE_RD_DIS
field.description: Set this bit to disable reading from BlOCK4-10.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_RTC_RAM_BOOT
field.description: Set this bit to disable boot from RTC RAM.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_ICACHE
field.description: Set this bit to disable Icache.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_USB_JTAG
field.description: Set this bit to disable function of usb switch to jtag in module of usb device.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_DOWNLOAD_ICACHE
field.description: Set this bit to disable Icache in download mode (boot_mode[3:0] is 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7).

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_USB_DEVICE
field.description: Set this bit to disable usb device.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_FORCE_DOWNLOAD
field.description: Set this bit to disable the function that forces chip into download mode.

field.name: EFUSE_RPT4_RESERVED6
field.description: Reserved (used for four backups method).

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_CAN
field.description: Set this bit to disable CAN function.

field.name: EFUSE_JTAG_SEL_ENABLE
field.description: Set this bit to enable selection between usb_to_jtag and pad_to_jtag through strapping gpio10 when both reg_dis_usb_jtag and reg_dis_pad_jtag are equal to 0.

field.name: EFUSE_SOFT_DIS_JTAG
field.description: Set these bits to disable JTAG in the soft way (odd number 1 means disable ). JTAG can be enabled in HMAC module.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_PAD_JTAG
field.description: Set this bit to disable JTAG in the hard way. JTAG is disabled permanently.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_DOWNLOAD_MANUAL_ENCRYPT
field.description: Set this bit to disable flash encryption when in download boot modes.

field.name: EFUSE_USB_DREFH
field.description: Controls single-end input threshold vrefh, 1.76 V to 2 V with step of 80 mV, stored in eFuse.

field.name: EFUSE_USB_DREFL
field.description: Controls single-end input threshold vrefl, 0.8 V to 1.04 V with step of 80 mV, stored in eFuse.

field.name: EFUSE_USB_EXCHG_PINS
field.description: Set this bit to exchange USB D+ and D- pins.

field.name: EFUSE_VDD_SPI_AS_GPIO
field.description: Set this bit to vdd spi pin function as gpio.

field.name: EFUSE_BTLC_GPIO_ENABLE
field.description: Enable btlc gpio.

field.name: EFUSE_POWERGLITCH_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable power glitch function.

field.name: EFUSE_POWER_GLITCH_DSENSE
field.description: Sample delay configuration of power glitch.

field.name: EFUSE_RPT4_RESERVED2
field.description: Reserved (used for four backups method).

field.name: EFUSE_WDT_DELAY_SEL
field.description: Selects RTC watchdog timeout threshold, in unit of slow clock cycle. 0: 40000. 1: 80000. 2: 160000. 3:320000.

field.name: EFUSE_SPI_BOOT_CRYPT_CNT
field.description: Set this bit to enable SPI boot encrypt/decrypt. Odd number of 1: enable. even number of 1: disable.

field.name: EFUSE_SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE0
field.description: Set this bit to enable revoking first secure boot key.

field.name: EFUSE_SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE1
field.description: Set this bit to enable revoking second secure boot key.

field.name: EFUSE_SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE2
field.description: Set this bit to enable revoking third secure boot key.

field.name: EFUSE_KEY_PURPOSE_0
field.description: Purpose of Key0.

field.name: EFUSE_KEY_PURPOSE_1
field.description: Purpose of Key1.

field.description: Purpose of Key2.

field.description: Purpose of Key3.

field.description: Purpose of Key4.

field.name: EFUSE_KEY_PURPOSE_5
field.description: Purpose of Key5.

field.name: EFUSE_RPT4_RESERVED3
field.description: Reserved (used for four backups method).

field.name: EFUSE_SECURE_BOOT_EN
field.description: Set this bit to enable secure boot.

field.name: EFUSE_SECURE_BOOT_AGGRESSIVE_REVOKE
field.description: Set this bit to enable revoking aggressive secure boot.

field.name: EFUSE_RPT4_RESERVED0
field.description: Reserved (used for four backups method).

field.name: EFUSE_FLASH_TPUW
field.description: Configures flash waiting time after power-up, in unit of ms. If the value is less than 15, the waiting time is the configurable value; Otherwise, the waiting time is twice the configurable value.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_DOWNLOAD_MODE
field.description: Set this bit to disable download mode (boot_mode[3:0] = 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7).

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_LEGACY_SPI_BOOT
field.description: Set this bit to disable Legacy SPI boot mode (boot_mode[3:0] = 4).

field.name: EFUSE_UART_PRINT_CHANNEL
field.description: Selectes the default UART print channel. 0: UART0. 1: UART1.

field.name: EFUSE_FLASH_ECC_MODE
field.description: Set ECC mode in ROM, 0: ROM would Enable Flash ECC 16to18 byte mode. 1:ROM would use 16to17 byte mode.

field.name: EFUSE_DIS_USB_DOWNLOAD_MODE
field.description: Set this bit to disable UART download mode through USB.

field.name: EFUSE_ENABLE_SECURITY_DOWNLOAD
field.description: Set this bit to enable secure UART download mode.

field.name: EFUSE_UART_PRINT_CONTROL
field.description: Set the default UARTboot message output mode. 00: Enabled. 01: Enabled when GPIO8 is low at reset. 10: Enabled when GPIO8 is high at reset. 11:disabled.

field.name: EFUSE_PIN_POWER_SELECTION
field.description: GPIO33-GPIO37 power supply selection in ROM code. 0: VDD3P3_CPU. 1: VDD_SPI.

field.name: EFUSE_FLASH_TYPE
field.description: Set the maximum lines of SPI flash. 0: four lines. 1: eight lines.

field.name: EFUSE_FLASH_PAGE_SIZE
field.description: Set Flash page size.

field.name: EFUSE_FLASH_ECC_EN
field.description: Set 1 to enable ECC for flash boot.

field.name: EFUSE_FORCE_SEND_RESUME
field.description: Set this bit to force ROM code to send a resume command during SPI boot.

field.name: EFUSE_SECURE_VERSION
field.description: Secure version (used by ESP-IDF anti-rollback feature).
